DualPathBaseline
================

Topology
- hostA -> r1 -> r2 -> r3 -> hostB
- backup branch: r1 -> r4 -> r3

Routing
- Primary path: hostA -> r1 -> r2 -> r3 -> hostB
- Backup path: hostA -> r1 -> r4 -> r3 -> hostB
- OSPF interface costs prefer the r1-r2-r3 branch and keep the r1-r4-r3 branch as a higher-cost alternative.

Goal
- Archival minimal OSPF sanity reference.
- Establish a deterministic OSPF topology for debugging only when the regional backbone path needs a tiny control case.
- This scenario is no longer a first-class dissertation workflow target; keep it stable and avoid extending it unless a specific validation question requires it.
